        <h1>LeetCode 3190: Find Minimum Operations to Make All Elements Divisible by Three (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums. In one operation, you can add or subtract 1 from any element of nums. Return the minimum number of operations to make all elements of nums divisible by 3.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3,4]<br/>
                Output: 3<br/>
                Explanation: All array elements can be made divisible by 3 using 3 operations: Subtract 1 from 1, Add 1 to 2, Subtract 1 from 4.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [3,6,9]<br/>
                Output: 0<br/>
                Explanation: All elements are already divisible by 3.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minimumOperations(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int operations = 0;
        
        for (int num : nums) {
            int remainder = num % 3;
            
            // If remainder is 1, we need 1 operation (subtract 1)
            // If remainder is 2, we need 1 operation (add 1)
            // If remainder is 0, we need 0 operations
            if (remainder != 0) {
                operations++;
            }
        }
        
        return operations;
    }
};</code></pre>
